      <p>Hi Molly, long-time reader and admirer here! I just wanted to say that I had the same experience as Kristin with this recipe, getting more of a batter than a dough: I mixed the dough up this morning using the weight measurements and my scale. My instinct was to add a bit more flour, but was afraid of ruining the texture since I had already used half all-purpose and half whole wheat flour (for a total of 155g)&#8230;so I smeared it onto some plastic wrap dusted with flour and put it in the fridge. Not sure what will be waiting for me when I get home later tonight, but if it hasn&#39;t hardened enough, my plan is to freeze the log before slicing and baking tomorrow morning to take with me to London to visit friends. Thanks for double-checking the weights for us, but any other thoughts or advice would be greatly appreciated!</p>
