  <li id="comment-35722" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">laurie</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/you-can-count-on-me/#comment-35722"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-01-15T22:12:21-05:00">Sunday, January 15, 2012 at 10:12 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hope the cold has left the premises by now! A few thoughts on the difference between the cookies&#8230;King Arthur all purpose is my go-to flour, but I had to buy another brand recently because the store was out. I couldn&#39;t believe the difference it has made in my recipes. In my biscuits, for example, using KA flour results in biscuits with a golden top and lighter bottoms. With the other flour, the tops were lighter and the bottoms were dark. I was so intrigued by this that I remade them with both flours on the same day to see if the results were the same, which they were. It would be interesting to find out if you were using the same flour, or a flour with a similar percentage of protein.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
