    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/11388111922637860319" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">jjk84</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/you-can-count-on-me/#comment-35732"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-01-18T09:13:25-05:00">Wednesday, January 18, 2012 at 9:13 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly, hope you&#39;re feeling better! I just wanted to follow up on the results of the cookie dough that was more like a batter &#8212; I have made two batches of these in the past week (for friends and colleagues!), and both times had the same results with the dough: it&#39;s sticky and soft, almost airy when it first comes together, but then chills perfectly into a firm, slice-and-bake cookie dough overnight in the fridge&#8230; and the cookies are DELICIOUS. Wonderously soft and tender in the center, with a slight crunch on the sides from the sugar and an intense chocolate flavor &#8211; all perfectly accented by the Maldon flakes. This is my new fave choc cookie recipe &#8212; thanks!!!</p>
    </div>

