    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I know we weren&#39;t supposed to compare&#8230;.but perhaps there were two types of choc. cookies on your boat trip? On the left,  I see chocolate crackly cookies with no sugar edge, that look like the Tartine recipe.  And on the right I see something that looks lighter and totally different, more sandy/sable like.  I just made the Tartine batter and there is nothing stiff about it.  I had already decided to leave out the leavening and milk to see if I could get a &#8220;sandier&#8221; cookie.  The batter was still way too wet and messy to roll nicely into a log.  But the batter tastes great.  Can&#39;t go wrong with chocolate and cocoa together.  Looking forward to baking them up.  But maybe you could check with Renee to see if there was more than one chocolate cookie in that box?</p>
