    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;m pretty sure the flour in my pantry jar was Arrowhead Mills Unbleached Organic. Like I said, I left out the milk and baking powder, as I was going for a less cakey texture.  Eggs and milk and baking powder are going to make a soft cookie.  But the recipe had melted choc and cocoa so I knew it would be good.  The dough wasn&#39;t batter thin, but very soft and globby, so didn&#39;t make a pretty log.  It sliced great after just  a few hours of chilling and the cookies were wonderful.  We loved them. Great flavor and texture.  I&#39;d make them again that way.</p>
