  <li id="comment-35751" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.dollopofcream.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Stephanie</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/01/you-can-count-on-me/#comment-35751"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-02-01T05:07:14-05:00">Wednesday, February 1, 2012 at 5:07 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just converted this recipe to gluten-free and they are absolutely wonderful &#8212; a pleasing dense, chewy, chocolately texture. </p>
<p>Instead of the flour, I used 40 g. sweet white sorghum flour, 35 g. GF oat flour, 40 g. sweet rice flour and 40 g. tapioca starch. </p>
<p>I also didn&#39;t plan far enough ahead, so I put them in the freezer for the first hour, then the fridge for 5 or 6 hours. They were lovely and easy to work with &#8212; and baked up a dream! </p>
<p>Oh, and I put in some chopped chocolate and loved it. Also loved Vancouver Island sea salt sprinkled on top . . . Definitely a cookie that will be in the standard rotation around our house. Thank you!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
